javax.activity
Class ServiceInformation

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--javax.activity.ServiceInformation
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public class ServiceInformation
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable

An instance of a ServiceInformation object is used by each ServiceManager to identify the name of the high-level service (HLS) and the context group to which a particular Activity belongs. This information is propagated as part of the org.omg.CosActivity.ActivityIdentity structure of the Activity service context, in the activity_specific_data field, when the type field of the ActivityIdentity is set to 0x4A324545 to indicate a J2EE Activity.
The activity_specific_data field is of type org.omg.CORBA.Any and, for a J2EE Activity type, contains a TypeCode with a TCKind of _tk_struct and a value of a j2ee_activity_specific_information structure which is defined in IDL as follows: 

  module javax
  {
    module activity
    {
      struct j2ee_activity_specific_data
      {
        string service_name;
        string context_group;
        any service_specific_data;
        any extended_data;
      };
    };
  };

Constructor Detail

ServiceInformation

public ServiceInformation(java.lang.String serviceName,
                          java.lang.String contextGroup,
                          java.io.Serializable serviceSpecificData)
Constructor used by a HLS to create a ServiceInformation object to hold the contents of a org.omg.CosActivity.ActivityIdentity.activity_specific_data.
This constructor is used by a HLS in order to provide this data to the Activity service to be propagated as part of an outbound Activity service context. The Activity service encapsulates the Serializable serviceSpecificData in a java.rmi.MarshalledObject to avoid class-loading problems when propagating ActivityIdentity structures containing this object.
Parameters:
serviceName - The name used to identify the high-level-service (HLS) to which an Activity belongs. This name is the URL to which the associated ServiceManager is bound in JNDI.
contextGroup - The name of the context-group to which all Activities of the HLS belong.
serviceSpecificData - Data that is specific to a particular HLS implementation. This parameter may be null.

Constructor used by the Activity service to create a ServiceInformation object to hold the contents of a org.omg.CosActivity.ActivityIdentity.activity_specific_data.
It is used by the Activity service when importing an Activity service context if the j2ee_activity_specific_data.service_specific_data field of that context contains a MarshalledObject.
Parameters:
serviceName - The name used to identify the high-level-service (HLS) to which an Activity belongs. This name is the URL to which the associated ServiceManager is bound in JNDI.
contextGroup - The name of the context-group to which all Activities of the HLS belong.
serviceSpecificData - Data that is specific to a particular HLS implementation. This parameter may be null.

Constructor used by the Activity service or HLS to create a ServiceInformation object to hold the contents of a org.omg.CosActivity.ActivityIdentity.activity_specific_data.
It is used by the Activity service when importing an Activity service context if the j2ee_activity_specific_data.service_specific_data field of that context does not contain a MarshalledObject.
It is also used by a HLS in order to provide this data to the Activity service to be propagated as part of an outbound Activity service context.
Parameters:
serviceName - The name used to identify the high-level-service (HLS) to which an Activity belongs. This name is the URL to which the associated ServiceManager is bound in JNDI.
contextGroup - The name of the context-group to which all Activities of the HLS belong.
serviceSpecificData - Data that is specific to a particular HLS implementation. This parameter may be null.
Method Detail

getServiceName

public java.lang.String getServiceName()
Returns a String that identifies the high-level-service (HLS) name. This name is the URL to which the associated ServiceManager is bound in JNDI.
Returns:
The JNDI name of the associated ServiceManager.

getContextGroup

public java.lang.String getContextGroup()
Returns the name of the context group to which all the ServiceManager's activities belong. This name is a String that different ServiceManagers use to identify a group to which their Activity contexts belong. By convention, a ServiceManager that does not intend its context to be managed cooperatively with transactions or another ServiceManager should use a ContextGroup name that is the same as the name of the service itself.
The returned value must not change if this method is called multiple times.
Returns:
The name of the context group that the ServiceManager's activities belong to. If no ContextGroup has been specified then this method returns null and the ServiceManager's activities belong to the default context group.

getServiceSpecificDataValue

public java.io.Serializable getServiceSpecificDataValue()
Returns a java.io.Serializable that contains information specific to the particular HLS ServiceManager. If the service-specific data is not a Serializable object then this method returns null and getServiceSpecificDataAny should be called instead.
The contents of the returned Serializable should not change if this method is called multiple times.
Returns:
A java.io.Serializable that contains information specific to the HLS. Returns null if the service-specific data is not a Serializable object or if there is no service-specific data data.

getServiceSpecificDataAny

public org.omg.CORBA.Any getServiceSpecificDataAny()
Returns a CORBA Any that contains information specific to the particular HLS ServiceManager.
The contents of the returned Any should not change if this method is called multiple times.
Returns:
A CORBA Any that contains information specific to the HLS.
Returns null if there is no service-specific data data.
